<HEADLINE> Man Dies in Shootout at University </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TERRE HAUTE, Ind. (AP) -- A former student at Indiana State  
University was shot and killed Monday by school officers who said 
he fired at them in trying to flee the scene of an attempted 
burglary. 
</P>
<P>
	Zedrick S. Johnson, 29, of Terre Haute, was seen climbing over  
an entrance to a student housing area on campus Monday morning, 
police said. The residential area is closed for spring break, but 
is open to a few students living there. 
</P>
<P>
	Police said they stopped Johnson and while questioning him, he  
told them he was carrying a gun. When they asked for the weapon, he 
ran, the officers said. 
</P>
<P>
	The officers caught up with Johnson in a back yard and he fired  
eight shots at them, they said. They returned fire, hitting Johnson 
six times. The officers were uninjured. 
</P>
<P>
	Preliminary findings by investigators indicated that the  
shooting was justified, police Chief Joe Newport said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
