</P>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Mitch Richmond scored 23 points and the  
Washington Wizards overcame a horrendous start yesterday to hand 
the Milwaukee Bucks their worst loss of the season, 98-86. Juwan 
Howard added 20 points and 11 rebounds, and Ben Wallace had a 
strong game off the bench with nine points and 13 rebounds for the 
Wizards. Ray Allen had 22 points for the Bucks. 

</P>
<P>
	Red Wings 3, Avalanche 1  
</P>
<P>
	DENVER (AP) -- Vyacheslav Kozlov and rookie Stacy Roest scored  
second-period goals and Norm Maracle had 21 saves, leading the 
Detroit Red Wings over the Colorado Avalanche 3-1 yesterday. 
Maracle, getting his second straight start, allowed only a 
third-period goal to Joe Sakic to snap the Red Wings' three-game 
losing streak and end Colorado's three-game winning streak. Patrick 
Roy had 25 saves for Colorado. 

</P>
