<HEADLINE> Girl's Tip Leads to Murder Arrests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHICAGO (AP) -- Three men wanted for two rape-slayings were  
arrested after the 10-year-old daughter of one of the suspects 
recognized her father on television, police said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	The suspects, including the girl's father, Ronald Hinton, were  
ordered held without bond Monday on charges of rape and murder. 
</P>
<P>
	The photo identified by the girl was taken by a surveillance  
camera at an automatic teller machine at the moment that one of the 
slain women's card was used. The photo was broadcast on television, 
and the girl told her teacher it was her father. School officials 
contacted police. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's fascinating that a very evil crime spree was basically  
stopped by something as innocent as a third-grader having a 
conversation with her teacher,'' said Assistant State's Attorney 
Thomas Epach. 
</P>
<P>
	Charged with first-degree murder, aggravated criminal sexual  
assault and home invasion were Hinton, 26, Ronald Sanders, 25, and 
David Wales, 26, all of Chicago. 
</P>
<P>
	All three are accused of raping and strangling Merceda Ares, 31,  
who was killed Feb. 13 in her apartment in Rogers Park, a 
neighborhood at Chicago's north city limits. 
</P>
<P>
	Hinton and Sanders are additionally charged with the rape and  
slaying of 36-year-old Keary Gagnier in Rogers Park in August. 
</P>
<P>
	Hinton is accused of using an ATM card belonging to one of the  
victims. Police picked up Hinton over the weekend based on his 
daughter's statement, which led to the arrest of Sanders and Wales. 
Police said that all three suspects have given statements 
implicating themselves. 
</P>
</TEXT>
