<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Southwest Starts Long Island Service </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DALLAS (AP) -- Southwest Airlines Co. has begun service in the  
New York area, one of the nation's busiest and most competitive 
markets for the airline industry. 
</P>
<P>
	The Dallas-based carrier started service Sunday from Long Island  
MacArthur Airport at Islip, N.Y., in its latest expansion into the 
northeastern corridor. 
</P>
<P>
	Airline analysts have said introduction of budget service in the  
New York area could translate into big savings for consumers. An 
unrestricted business ticket on shuttles by US Airways or Delta Air 
Lines from New York to Boston or Washington cost about $200 each 
way. Southwest is more likely to charge about $70 each way. 
</P>
<P>
	The first service to Islip brought more than 100 passengers from  
Tampa, Fla., to Long Island. 
</P>
<P>
	MacArthur is located about 40 miles east of New York's LaGuardia  
Airport. 

</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
