<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Four Killed in Campsite Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BAXLEY, Ga. (AP) -- A portable heater left running inside a  
zipped-up tent apparently led to the carbon monoxide deaths of four 
campers, including three children, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
	Douglas S. Green, 51, his son, Adrian, 10, Clarence Williams, 9,  
and Nicolette Hawkins, 7, were found dead in their tent Sunday. 
Clarence and Nicolette were the adopted children of Green's 
common-law wife. 
</P>
<P>
	Autopsy results are expected next week.  
</P>
</TEXT>
