<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-15 06:15:12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Three Men Charged in Rape-Slayings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHICAGO (AP) -- Police charged three men in connection with two  
rape-slayings after being tipped off by a 10-year-old who 
recognized her father's picture on television. 
</P>
<P>
	The 3rd-grader recognized her father and a friend when  
surveillance pictures of three men were shown on the evening news 
Wednesday, police said Sunday. The next day, the girl told her 
teacher and school officials contacted police. 
</P>
<P>
	``That tip gave us their names,'' said Lt. Nick Nickeas.  
``That's how we picked them up.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Keary Gagnier, 36, was killed in August and Merceda Ares, 31,  
was found dead in her apartment on Feb. 17, investigators said. 
Both women, who lived alone, were raped, robbed and strangled. 
</P>
<P>
	Seeking help from the public in solving the crimes, police gave  
television stations pictures from surveillance cameras at automatic 
teller machines where unidentified men allegedly used bank and 
credit cards belonging to the two women. 
</P>
<P>
	Police would not say whose daughter provided the tip. Two men --  
Ronald Hinton, 26, of Chicago and Michael Sanders, 25, of Evanston 
-- were charged with murder, criminal sexual assault, and home 
invasion in both slayings. The third, David Wales, 26, of Chicago, 
was charged with the same counts in connection with Ms. Ares' 
death. 
</P>
<P>
	Police said DNA evidence linked the three men to the crimes. The  
men also allegedly used Ms. Ares' bank card and Ms. Gagnier's 
credit card on numerous occasions. 
</P>
<P>
	Hinton and Sanders were arrested Thursday. Under questioning,  
the two men then implicated Wales, according to authorities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
