<HEADLINE> `Analyze This' Rubs Out Competition / Box Office  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- The mobster comedy ``Analyze This'' held off  
``The Rage: Carrie 2'' and four other new films to remain on top of 
the North American box office, final figures showed Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	Starring Robert De Niro as a crime figure with emotional issues  
and Billy Crystal as his therapist, ``Analyze This'' grossed $15.6 
million, more than double the closest competitor, ``Carrie 2,'' 
which debuted with $7.1 million. 
</P>
<P>
	``Cruel Intentions'' tumbled 46 percent in its second week to  
finish third with $7 million. 
</P>
<P>
	It was followed by four new films, all doing mediocre business.  
</P>
<P>
	``The Corruptor'' opened in fourth with $5.8 million, ``Baby  
Geniuses'' in fifth with $5.6 million, ``The Deep End of the 
Ocean'' in sixth with $5.56 million and ``Wing Commander'' in 
seventh with $5.1 million. 
</P>
<P>
	Overall, the box office was down 7.5 percent from the same  
weekend last year, when ``Titanic'' was still going strong. 
</P>
<P>
	Here are the top 10 movies at North American theaters Friday  
