<HEADLINE> San Jose's Shields NHL Player of Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- San Jose Sharks goaltender Steve Shields is the  
NHL's latest player of the week. 
</P>
<P>
	Shields had a 3-0-0 record, 1.33 goals-against average, shutout  
and a .948 save percentage during the week ending March 14. 
</P>
<P>
	Shields edged Nashville Predators center Sebastien Bordeleau  
(four goals, three assists), Ottawa Senators center Alexei Yashin 
(five goals, one assist), Pittsburgh Penguins right wing Jaromir 
Jagr (three goals, four assists), and Calgary Flames defenseman 
Phil Housley (one goal, four assists). 
</P>
<P>
	Shields stopped 26 shots Friday night for his second career  
shutout in a 2-0 decision over the Detroit Red Wings. San Jose, 
which moved into seventh place in the Western Conference during the 
week, acquired Shields in June of 1998 from Buffalo. 
</P>
</TEXT>
