	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Legislation establishing quotas on steel  
imports has gained the backing of nearly half of the House despite 
signs that the domestic industry's outlook is brightening. That 
strong support in a Republican-led Congress that usually opposes 
restrictions on free trade reflects a belief that the turnaround is 
only temporary and that much larger layoffs loom if the federal 
government doesn't do something soon. A House vote is scheduled 
Wednesday. 

</P>
