money it received for fiscal years 1997 and 1998, combined, in millions. 
The House Ways and Means Committee says states have a total of $6.2 
billion in unspent welfare money, but that counts money that states 
have already obligated for specific payments. Counting only unobligated 
money, the total is just over $3 billion: 

