<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Stocks Rise; Dow Up 67 / Wall Street Report  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- The Dow Jones industrial average resumed its  
advance on 10,000 today as a new round of corporate mergers sent 
stock prices higher. 
</P>
<P>
	At noon on Wall Street, the Dow was up 67.44 at 9,943.79. The  
index of blue-chip stocks has flirted with 10,000 in recent 
sessions, coming within 42 points of that milestone Friday before 
giving up ground. 
</P>
<P>
	Broader stock indicators were mostly higher today.  
</P>
<P>
	After stocks sputtered in the first hour of trading, analysts  
said the market appeared to be awaiting a catalyst powerful enough 
to spark a strong run past 10,000. By midday, announcements of 
several big mergers provided that spark 
</P>
<P>
	The $16 billion acquisition of BankBoston Corp. by Fleet  
Financial Group Inc. added some punch to the financial services 
sector. Shares of BankBoston rose 1 1/16. Fleet, however, slipped 1 
15/16 to 42 13/16. 
</P>
<P>
	Also today, chemical giant DuPont Co. said it will pay $7.7  
billion to acquire 80 percent of Pioneer Hi-Bred International 
Inc., the world's largest seed corn company. 
</P>
<P>
	Airline stocks benefited from a new round of fare increases,  
which will push up the price of a business fare about 1 percent and 
a leisure fare about 3 percent. UAL Corp., which also indicated its 
first-quarter earnings will top analysts' expectations, was up 4 3/4 
at 71 13/16. 
</P>
<P>
	Oil stocks were among the decliners today, having rallied Friday  
as world oil producers agreed to cut their output. Chevron was off 
9/16 at 84 1/8, and Exxon was off 1/4 at 73 11/16. 
</P>
<P>
	The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 index was up 10.12 at 1,304.71, and  
the technology-heavy Nasdaq composite index was up 34.26 at 
2,415.79. 
</P>
<P>
	Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by an 7-to-6 margin on  
the New York Stock Exchange, where volume came to 325.6 million 
shares, slightly off Friday's pace. 
</P>
<P>
	The NYSE composite index was up 3.29 at 614.83, and the American  
Stock Exchange composite index was down 0.03 at 721.18. 
</P>
<P>
	Stocks rallied sharply overnight in Japan, as the Nikkei reached  
its highest level since last summer, rising 2 percent. 
</P>
<P>
	In afternoon trading, Germany's DAX index was down 0.2 percent,  
Britain's FT-SE 100 was down .1 percent and France's CAC-40 was 
down 0.4 percent. 

</P>
</TEXT>
