<HEADLINE> Yankees' Petitte Resumes Throwing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TAMPA, Fla. (AP) -- New York Yankees left-hander Andy Pettitte  
took a small step forward today. 
</P>
<P>
	Pettitte reported no problems after playing catch for the first  
time since leaving his spring debut after one inning March 7 
because of a muscle strain in his throwing elbow. 
</P>
<P>
	``I didn't feel anything,'' said Pettitte, who might throw off a  
mound later this week. ``The biggest test is stepping on the mound, 
taking five minutes off and cranking it up again.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Pettitte is scheduled to play catch again Tuesday before leaving  
the team to attend his grandfather's funeral Wednesday in Baton 
Rouge, La. 
</P>
