<HEADLINE> IBP To Make Its Own Meat Products </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DAKOTA CITY, Neb. (AP) -- IBP Inc., the world's largest supplier  
of fresh beef and pork to stores and restaurants, plans to expand 
its reach directly onto grocery shelves with its own brand of meat 
products. 
</P>
<P>
	The company announced Monday that it has hired an advertising  
firm to create a national brand name for a new line of uncooked and 
cooked beef and pork products. 
</P>
<P>
	``We want to be the preferred meat brand in categories in which  
we compete,'' IBP spokesman Gary Mickelson said. 
</P>
<P>
	In another step toward diversification, IBP said last week it  
will purchase H&AMP;M Food Systems Co. from Specialty Foods Corp. of 
Deerfield, Ill. H&AMP;M produces pizza toppings, soups, sauces and side 
dishes for restaurants and other food service companies. 
</P>
<P>
	IBP has 45 plants in North America and employs more than 40,000  
people, 


</P>
