<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> `Analyze This' Rubs Out Competition / Box Office  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- The mobster comedy ``Analyze This'' held off  
``The Rage: Carrie 2'' and four other new films to remain on top of 
the North American box office, final figures showed Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	Starring Robert De Niro as a crime figure with emotional issues  
and Billy Crystal as his therapist, ``Analyze This'' grossed $15.6 
million, more than double the closest competitor, ``Carrie 2,'' 
which debuted with $7.1 million. 
</P>
<P>
	``Cruel Intentions'' tumbled 46 percent in its second week to  
finish third with $7 million. 
</P>
<P>
	It was followed by four new films, all doing mediocre business.  
</P>
<P>
	``The Corruptor'' opened in fourth with $5.8 million, ``Baby  
Geniuses'' in fifth with $5.6 million, ``The Deep End of the 
Ocean'' in sixth with $5.56 million and ``Wing Commander'' in 
seventh with $5.1 million. 
</P>
<P>
	Overall, the box office was down 7.5 percent from the same  
weekend last year, when ``Titanic'' was still going strong. 
</P>
<P>
	Here are the top 10 movies at North American theaters Friday  
through Sunday, followed by studio, gross, number of theater 
locations, average receipts per location, total gross and number of 
weeks in release, as compiled by Exhibitor Relations Co. Inc. and 
ACNielsen EDI Inc.: 
</P>
<P>
	1. ``Analyze This,'' Warner Bros., $15.6 million, 2,537  
locations, $6,136 average, $39.9 million, two weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	2. ``The Rage: Carrie 2,'' MGM/UA, $7.1 million, 2,286  
locations, $3,091 average, $7.1 million, one week. 
</P>
<P>
	3. ``Cruel Intentions,'' Sony, $7 million, 2,312 locations,  
$3,031 average, $23.4 million, two weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	4. ``The Corruptor,'' New Line, $5.8 million, 1,804 locations,  
$3,196, $5.8 million, one week. 
</P>
<P>
	5. ``Baby Geniuses,'' Sony, $5.6 million, 1,689 locations,  
$3,324 average, $5.6 million, one week. 
</P>
<P>
	6. ``The Deep End of the Ocean,'' Sony, $5.56 million, 1,907  
locations, $2,915 average, $5.56 million, one week. 
</P>
<P>
	7. ``Wing Commander,'' 20th Century Fox, $5.1 million, 2,019  
locations, $2,533 average, $5.1 million, one week. 
</P>
<P>
	8. ``The Other Sister,'' Disney, $3.8 million, 1,863 locations,  
$2,061 average, $19.9 million, three weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	9. ``8mm,'' Sony, $3.5 million, 2,241 locations, $1,571 average,  
$31 million, three weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	10. ``October Sky,'' Universal, $3 million, 1,583 locations,  
$1,900 average, $20.8 million, four weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	11. ``Shakespeare in Love,'' Miramax, $2.8 million, 1,405  
locations, $2,028 average, $68.9 million, 14 weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	12. ``Payback,'' Paramount, $2.5 million, 1,982 locations,  
$1,276 average, $75.9 million, six weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	13. ``My Favorite Martian,'' Disney, $1.9 million, 1,880  
locations, $1,009 average, $32.8 million, five weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	14. ``Life is Beautiful,'' Miramax, $1.87 million, 646  
locations, $2,888 average, $32.8 million, 21 weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	15. ``Message in a Bottle,'' Warner Bros., $1.8 million, 1,876  
locations, $980 average, $49.4 million, five weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	16. ``She's All That,'' Miramax, $1.3 million, 1,406 locations,  
$921 average, $59.2 million, seven weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	17. ``Saving Private Ryan,'' DreamWorks, $858,625, 616  
locations, $1,394 average, $208.7 million, 34 weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	18. ``Rushmore,'' Disney, $646,259, 446 locations, $1,449  
average, $15.2 million, six weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	19. ``Blast from the Past,'' New Line, $645,784, 1,001  
locations, $645 average, $24.7 million, five weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	20. ``Elizabeth,'' Gramercy, $559,754, 340 locations, $1,646  
average, $26.9 million, 19 weeks. 
</P>
