<HEADLINE> Pippen Wants To Be More Involved </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HOUSTON (AP) -- Scottie Pippen is getting exasperated with his  
role -- or lack of one -- with the Houston Rockets. 
</P>
<P>
	Pippen took only five shots and scored four points in 35 minutes  
in Sunday's 104-90 loss to the Phoenix Suns. Afterward, he wondered 
why the Rockets signed him to a five-year, $67.5 million contract 
if they didn't intend to use his services to the fullest. 
</P>
<P>
	He's averaging 40.6 minutes per game, fourth in the NBA.  
</P>
<P>
	``I'm frustrated,'' Pippen told the Houston Chronicle following  
the loss. ``Playing the minutes I'm playing I'm not involved in the 
offense. It makes the game not fun anymore. My next step is to find 
why this organization wanted me. 
</P>
<P>
	``I want to sit down and ask, `What's my position on this ball  
club?' If it's just from a defensive standpoint, then I can 
understand the point, then I can feel much better.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Pippen, a seven-time All-Star in 11 seasons with the Chicago  
Bulls, said he did not regret his decision to sign with the Rockets 
but wants to be more involved. 
</P>
<P>
	``We have to get everybody involved,'' Pippen said. ``We have to  
make the game for everybody. There's nights when things are not 
going right. It's time to go to somebody else and get somebody else 
involved. 
</P>
<P>
	``Games like tonight (Sunday) make the game very difficult.''  
</P>
